rules:
- "Use TypeScript by default."
- "Prefer Tailwind utility classes for styling."
- "Use HeroUI (NextUI v2) components where appropriate."
- "Keep code production-ready, typed, minimal, and accessible (a11y)."
- "Write smaller, composable components."
- "No external CSS frameworks beyond Tailwind unless asked."
- "Prefer server components in Next.js unless client-specific features are required."
- "When uncertain, ask for a brief confirmation with options."


style:
- "Consistent import order: react, next, libs, components, styles."
- "Use named exports where possible; default export only for top-level pages/roots."
- "Function components with explicit props types."
- "Use async/await; avoid .then chains."


security:
- "Do not commit secrets; use .env and .env.example."
- "Validate all input server-side; sanitize any user-generated HTML."